

This directory contains many examples for using nauyaca along with many other python tools. All input files (as planet ephemeris) are stored in the folder named 'inputs'. For many examples the same transit ephemeris are used. We recommend running these examples in the same order as listed here.
These examples show many extra features hosted in nauyaca. A more detailed explanation of the nauyaca's modules can be seen at Documentation.


--> A brief description of these examples:

** quick_fit.py: Perform the fit of a two-planets system using the optimization module and MCMC. Generate a pair of built-in figures to visualize the results.



** custom_fit.py: Perform the fit of a three-planets system using a prior given by the user. It is introduced other features in nauyaca to customize the fitting process
